narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A good amount of work, but not enough to make you feel lost.
This is a class with quite a lot of reading, kanji and grammar. If you love Japanese, I definitely recommend it. If not, the time commitment is probably too much.

If you want to take a straightforward Japanese language class, this is the class to take. The classroom materials aren't that engaging, but it's a pretty good way to keep up your spoken and written Japanese.
I highly recommend this class to those who are motivated to understand not only Japanese but also their culture. This class gives you more than a understanding of Japanese.
